description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Nurse Assessing and Reviewing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to join St. Luke’s Hospice Community Services team which includes OneResponse - providing triage and rapid response visits, Rapid Assessment and Discharge Service managing palliative discharges and assessing and reviewing RADS care support, and Hospice at Home full assessments and planning of care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be a vital part of the specialist team ensuring the highest standard of holistic palliative care is delivered to patients and families in South West Essex. The post holder will support the patient and his/her family ensuring seamless support, working flexibly in Rapid Assessment and Discharge, One Response and Hospice at Home as needed and utilising excellent clinical skills, triaging and Holistic Nursing Assessment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a 7 weeks leave (inclusive of bank holidays), a friendly working environment within a supportive team and the opportunity to continue in the NHS Pension if already a member.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A valid clean driver&#39;s licence and use of own vehicle is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information please ring Gill Booth on 01268 526259.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date for receipt of applications: 9th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is subject to DBS Disclosure&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We also offer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Funded Clinical Supervision&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free flu jabs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Discounted gym membership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Home cooked staff meals cooked on site at subsidised rate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Variable shift pattern with flexibly to meet your needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Central location in Basildon close to major road networks and within walking distance of Basildon Station.,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pension package, opportunity to continue in the NHS Pension if already a member.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;27 days annual leave, in addition to public holidays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent commitment to learning and development including external training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Active Staff Wellbeing programme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
